Police operatives in Niger State have arrested a 25-year-old man, Abubakar Mohammed Buba for allegedly conspiring to kill his father, Alhaji Mohammed Buba.
  
Spokesperson for Niger State Police Command, DSP Wasiu Abiodun, in a statement, yesterday, said the suspect was arrested on December 29, based on credible intelligence.
  
According to him, police operatives attached to Chanchaga Division in Bosso Local Council of the state arrested Abubakar Mohammed Buba of Gidan Madara area in Chanchaga, Minna. 